\section{Anellini}

The diminutive {\sl onellini} (small rings) are part of the extended
{\sl postine minute} (tiny pasta) clan. Their thickness varies between
only 1.15 and 1.20 mm, and the are therefore usually found in light
soups together with croutons and thinly sliced vegetables. This pasta
may also be found served in a {\sl timballo} (baked pasta dish).

