pastasciutta} (pasta boiled, drained, and dished up with a sauce,
rather than in broth). Its best known accompaniment is {\sl
amatriciana}: a hearty traditional sauce made with dried port,
Pecorino Romano and tomato sauce, and named after the medieval town of
